{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Conversation history is trimmed to the most recent 10 messages before the LLM call when history is too long.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: the failure boundary is module handoff (history manager -> LLM request builder), not pure algorithm-only logic. A unit test of a trim helper can miss wiring bugs (wrong field, wrong order, untrimmed payload). REAL-INFRA/MOCK-HIDE: no real OS/network/subprocess is required; an in-process fake LLM client that captures request payload is sufficient. LLM-DEP: no dependence on model output quality. REJECTION-GATE: System is disqualified by behavior text focusing on payload trimming only (no timeout/network/OS behavior). Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because the behavior does not evaluate model decisions, only what is sent.","test_description":"Wire chatbot service with a fake LLM transport that records request messages. Provide >10-message history, execute one request, and assert the LLM payload contains exactly the latest 10 messages in correct order and excludes older ones.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Generated response addresses the customer’s question instead of being generic/off-topic.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: correctness is response quality/relevance, which depends on real model behavior and can vary across runs/prompts. A stubbed response would always pass and hide the real failure. REAL-INFRA: no special OS/subprocess need beyond making model calls. MULTI-STEP: this behavior is single-step quality, not a chained agent pipeline. REJECTION-GATE: Workflow is disqualified because behavior text asks only for one generation’s relevance, not multi-step handoff correctness.","test_description":"Run real model generation on a labeled set of customer questions and score whether