work/process failure behavior. Agentic is disqualified because assertions are storage/timestamp integrity, not model judgment quality.","test_description":"Execute service with deterministic generated/re-generated responses against a real local test DB, then assert stored records include user input, all drafts/regenerations, and expected timestamp fields/order.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"If tone-check regeneration occurs, only the second response is customer-visible; rejected draft is never shown.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"MULTI-STEP: this is end-to-end handoff across multiple agentic stages (initial generation -> tone decision -> regeneration -> delivery selection). The failure appears in sequencing/state propagation, not a single function. INTEGRATION-BRAKE(d): behavior is explicitly orchestration across LLM-involved stages; keeping Integration would miss failures where real model outputs/timing cause draft leakage. Agentic alone is close, but this behavior requires validating the chained pipeline outcome across more than one model-driven step. REJECTION-GATE: lower levels are disqualified by behavior text explicitly coupling trigger and replacement outcome ('when tone check triggers regeneration, the second response replaces the first').","test_description":"Run full pipeline with real model/tone-check on cases that trigger regeneration; assert customer-facing channel/output contains only regenerated text, while rejected draft exists only in internal logs/audit records.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.25,"Workflow":0.6}}]}
